casebody.data:
Argued and submitted September 23, STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. GLEN R. DEAN, Appellant. (C95-01-30010; CA A90429) 926 P2d 336 David C. Degner, Deputy Public Defender, argued the cause for appellant. With him on the brief was Sally L. Avera, Public Defender. Timothy A. Sylwester, Assistant Attorney General, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Theodore R. Kulongoski, Attorney General, and Virginia L. Linder, Solicitor General. PER CURIAM

convictions affirmed; remanded for resentencing November 13, 1996

Before Warren, Presiding Judge, and Edmonds and Armstrong, Judges.
